{"name":"Canâ€™t Keep A Mad Man Down","permission":{"default":0,"ZhC8ATjW2zJWoMct":3},"type":"move","data":{"name":"","description":"<p>Can&rsquo;t Keep A Mad Man Down</p>\n<p>Requires: Undying One</p>\n<p>When you r each 0 hit points while raging, you may choose not to roll your Last Breath. If you do, you stay alive until your rage ends.</p>\n<p>When your rage ends, make your Last Breath, except roll [[/r 3d6]] and use the worst two results.</p>","class":"The Berserker","rollType":"","rollMod":0,"requiresLevel":6,"requiresMove":"Undying One","moveType":"advanced","moveGroup":""},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"MKUW1uI0okJxQybd"}
{"name":"Steam Vent","permission":{"default":0,"ZhC8ATjW2zJWoMct":3},"type":"move","data":{"name":"","description":"<p>Steam Vent</p>\n<p>While raging, you may spend 1 Fury to deal 1d6 damage to an enemy in the near range.</p>","class":"The Berserker","rollType":"","rollMod":0,"requiresLevel":6,"requiresMove":"","moveType":"advanced","moveGroup":""},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"DWZQQUx77BY3XrT1"}
{"name":"Pariah","permission":{"default":0,"ZhC8ATjW2zJWoMct":3},"type":"move","data":{"name":"","description":"<p>Pariah</p>\n<p>When you make yourself the target of a community&rsquo;s hatred, mark 3 Fury.</p>\n<p>The GM will tell you who you&rsquo;ve spared or saved from a similar fate.</p>","class":"The Berserker","rollType":"","rollMod":0,"requiresLevel":6,"requiresMove":"","moveType":"advanced","moveGroup":""},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"UW74WvcTt30gp66z"}
{"name":"Maw of Chaos","permission":{"default":0,"ZhC8ATjW2zJWoMct":3},"type":"move","data":{"name":"","description":"<p>Maw of Chaos</p>\n<p>While raging, your mouth is a weapon with the tags hand, messy, and 2 piercing.</p>\n<p>If this attack would kill someone, you may consume them and heal [[/r 1d10]] damage.</p>","class":"The Berserker","rollType":"","rollMod":0,"requiresLevel":6,"requiresMove":"","moveType":"advanced","moveGroup":""},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"qfgcPwix1OXENGOW"}
{"name":"Herald Of The Storm","permission":{"default":0,"ZhC8ATjW2zJWoMct":3},"type":"move","data":{"name":"","description":"<p>Herald Of The Storm</p>\n<p>Your anger i s one of the forces of the universe. Choose a tag to describe the forces or elements that radiate from you while you rage.</p>\n<p>Whenever you deal damage or gain Fury while raging, you deal [[/r 1d6]] additional</p>\n<p>damage of that tag to everything close.</p>\n<p>This damage doesn&rsquo;t cause you to lose Fury.</p>","class":"The Berserker","rollType":"","rollMod":0,"requiresLevel":6,"requiresMove":"","moveType":"advanced","moveGroup":""},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"ZxxTgoSfeEsrK9R4"}
{"name":"Lycanthropy Is A Strong Word","permission":{"default":0,"ZhC8ATjW2zJWoMct":3},"type":"move","data":{"name":"","description":"<p>Lycanthropy Is A Strong Word</p>\n<p>Requires: Animal Totem</p>\n<p>When you rage, your form changes to honor and emulate your animal totem.</p>\n<p>Describe what form you take to your GM, and they will give you three animal moves - you can spend 1 Fury while raging to make those moves.</p>","class":"The Berserker","rollType":"","rollMod":0,"requiresLevel":6,"requiresMove":"Animal Totem","moveType":"advanced","moveGroup":""},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"h1EVYblx1Cj9vkKK"}
